{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775882670417,"sessionID":"ses_285255de5ffes5chFbBEceByDE","part":{"id":"prt_d7adb0c2a001FqphSn0rg9f7c3","messageID":"msg_d7adaf800001QIMczXcRjv36XB","sessionID":"ses_285255de5ffes5chFbBEceByDE","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_6686fe5954d940fc885b93fc","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-033/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-033/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-033: Makefile 构建目标体系\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: 本提案实现 AgentCube 项目的 Makefile 构建目标体系，为 Docker 镜像构建、推送、验证、测试提供标准化的自动化命令。该 Makefile 是 AgentCube 容器化工作流的核心入口，支撑开发、CI/CD、生产环境的镜像生命周期管理。\n6: \n7: 目标是：\n8: \n9: 1. **构建自动化** - 提供统一的 `make` 命令简化 Docker 镜像构建流程，减少手动操作错误\n10: 2. **目标分层** - 支持全量构建 (`docker-build-all`) 和单组件构建 (`docker-build-workloadmanager` 等)，适应不同场景\n11: 3. **推送标准化** - 统一镜像推送流程，自动关联 VERSION、COMMIT_SHA、DOCKER_TAG 多标签\n12: 4. **集群集成** - 提供 Kind 集群加载目标 (`kind-load-all`)，支持本地开发测试\n13: 5. **多架构支持** - 集成 Docker Buildx，支持 amd64、arm64 多架构镜像构建\n14: 6. **质量门禁** - 内置镜像验证 (`docker-validate`) 和测试 (`docker-test`) 目标，确保镜像质量\n15: 7. **清理工具** - 提供本地镜像清理目标 (`docker-clean`)，减少磁盘占用\n16: \n17: 本提案基于 existing Makefile (仅包含 Docker 相关目标) 进行扩展，遵循 Makefile 最佳实践和 AR-032 Dockerfile 多阶段构建规范。\n18: \n19: ## Scope\n20: \n21: **Module:** root  \n22: **Language:** Makefile  \n23: **Size:** M\n24: \n25: 本 AR 包含：\n26: \n27: - **包含内容：**\n28:   - Makefile 根文件更新 - 扩展构建目标体系\n29:   - 构建目标 (build) - `docker-build-all`, `docker-build-*`\n30:   - 推送目标 (push) - `docker-push-all`, `docker-push-*`\n31:   - Kind 加载目标 (kind-load) - `kind-load-all`, `kind-load-*`\n32:   - 多架构目标 (buildx) - `docker-buildx-all`, `docker-buildx-*`\n33:   - 验证目标 (validate) - `docker-validate`, `docker-validate-*`\n34:   - 测试目标 (test) - `docker-test`, `docker-test-build`, `docker-test-runtime`\n35:   - 清理目标 (clean) - `docker-clean`\n36:   - 帮助目标 (help) - 打印可用目标和变量\n37:   - 配置变量 - `DOCKER_REGISTRY`, `DOCKER_TAG`, `VERSION`, `COMMIT_SHA`\n38: \n39: - **不包含内容：**\n40:   - Dockerfile 编写（由 AR-032 管理）\n41:   - Helm Chart 构建（由 AR-030 管理）\n42:   - CI/CD 流水线配置\n43:   - Go/Python 应用编译目标（已有独立 Makefile 或命令）\n44: \n45: ## Current State Analysis\n46: \n47: ### 现有 Makefile 状态\n48: \n49: 根据根目录 `Makefile` (237 行)，当前已实现：\n50: \n51: **已有目标：**\n52: - `docker-build-all`, `docker-build-workloadmanager`, `docker-build-router`, `docker-build-picod` - 构建目标\n53: - `docker-push-all`, `docker-push-workloadmanager`, `docker-push-router`, `docker-push-picod` - 推送目标\n54: - `kind-load-all`, `kind-load-workloadmanager`, `kind-load-router`, `kind-load-picod` - Kind 加载目标\n55: - `docker-buildx-all`, `docker-buildx-workloadmanager`, `docker-buildx-router`, `docker-buildx-picod` - 多架构目标\n56: - `docker-clean` - 清理目标\n57: - `docker-validate`, `docker-validate-*` - 验证目标\n58: - `docker-test`, `docker-test-build`, `docker-test-runtime` - 测试目标\n59: - `help` - 帮助信息\n60: \n61: **已有变量：**\n62: - `DOCKER_REGISTRY` (默认：ghcr.io/volcano-sh)\n63: - `DOCKER_TAG` (默认：latest)\n64: - `VERSION` (从 git tag 获取)\n65: - `COMMIT_SHA` (从 git rev-parse 获取)\n66: \n67: **镜像命名：**\n68: - `WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE` = $(DOCKER_REGISTRY)/workloadmanager\n69: - `ROUTER_IMAGE` = $(DOCKER_REGISTRY)/router\n70: - `PICOD_IMAGE` = $(DOCKER_REGISTRY)/picod\n71: \n72: ### 差距分析\n73: \n74: 当前 Makefile 已经比较完善，但根据 AR-033 的\"构建目标体系\"要求，需要：\n75: \n76: 1. **目标文档化** - 缺少目标依赖关系图和执行顺序说明\n77: 2. **测试脚本集成** - 验证脚本和测试脚本依赖外部文件 (`deployment/docker/test/validate.sh` 等)，需要确保这些文件存在\n78: 3. **错误处理** - 部分目标缺少错误处理（如 `docker-clean` 使用 `-` 前缀忽略错误，但其他目标未处理）\n79: 4. **可扩展性** - 新增组件时需要手动添加多个目标，缺少自动化生成机制\n80: 5. **PHONY 声明** - 所有目标都已声明为 `.PHONY`，符合最佳实践\n81: \n82: ### 参考设计规范\n83: \n84: 根据 AR-032 proposal.md 和项目结构：\n85: \n86: **Makefile 要求：**\n87: - 支持三个组件：Workload Manager、Router、Picod\n88: - 镜像标签：latest, <commit-sha>, <version>\n89: - 基础镜像：distroless/static-debian11\n90: - 构建优化：多阶段构建，CGO_ENABLED=0\n91: \n92: **验证脚本要求：**\n93: - 检查镜像大小 (< 50MB)\n94: - 检查层数 (<= 5)\n95: - 检查非 root 用户\n96: - 检查端口暴露\n97: - 检查健康检查配置\n98: \n99: ### 需要补充的文件\n100: \n101: 根据 Makefile 中引用的脚本：\n102: \n103: 1. `deployment/docker/test/validate.sh` - 镜像验证脚本\n104: 2. `deployment/docker/test/build_test.sh` - 构建测试脚本\n105: 3. `deployment/docker/test/runtime_test.sh` - 运行时测试脚本\n106: \n107: 这些脚本当前不存在，需要创建。\n108: \n109: ## Proposed Changes\n110: \n111: ### 1. Makefile 目标体系结构\n112: \n113: ```\n114: Makefile 目标层次结构\n115: \n116: 1. 构建目标 (Build)\n117:    ├── docker-build-all           # 构建所有镜像\n118:    ├── docker-build-workloadmanager\n119:    ├── docker-build-router\n120:    └── docker-build-picod\n121: \n122: 2. 推送目标 (Push)\n123:    ├── docker-push-all            # 推送所有镜像\n124:    ├── docker-push-workloadmanager\n125:    ├── docker-push-router\n126:    └── docker-push-picod\n127: \n128: 3. Kind 加载目标 (Kind Load)\n129:    ├── kind-load-all              # 加载所有镜像到 Kind\n130:    ├── kind-load-workloadmanager\n131:    ├── kind-load-router\n132:    └── kind-load-picod\n133: \n134: 4. 多架构目标 (Buildx)\n135:    ├── docker-buildx-all          # 多架构构建所有\n136:    ├── docker-buildx-workloadmanager\n137:    ├── docker-buildx-router\n138:    └── docker-buildx-picod\n139: \n140: 5. 验证目标 (Validate)\n141:    ├── docker-validate            # 验证所有镜像\n142:    ├── docker-validate-workloadmanager\n143:    ├── docker-validate-router\n144:    └── docker-validate-picod\n145: \n146: 6. 测试目标 (Test)\n147:    ├── docker-test                # 运行所有测试\n148:    ├── docker-test-build          # 构建测试\n149:    └── docker-test-runtime        # 运行时测试\n150: \n151: 7. 清理目标 (Clean)\n152:    └── docker-clean               # 清理本地镜像\n153: \n154: 8. 帮助目标 (Help)\n155:    └── help                       # 打印帮助信息\n156: ```\n157: \n158: ### 2. 现有 Makefile 保持不变\n159: \n160: 当前 Makefile 已经实现了完整的目标体系，无需修改。重点补充缺失的脚本文件。\n161: \n162: ### 3. 创建验证脚本\n163: \n164: ```bash\n165: #!/bin/bash\n166: # deployment/docker/test/validate.sh\n167: # Validate Docker image for size, layers, security, ports, healthcheck\n168: \n169: set -e\n170: \n171: IMAGE=\"${1:-}\"\n172: \n173: if [ -z \"$IMAGE\" ]; then\n174:     echo \"Usage: $0 <image-name>\"\n175:     exit 1\n176: fi\n177: \n178: echo \"Validating image: $IMAGE\"\n179: echo \"\"\n180: \n181: # Check if image exists\n182: if ! docker image inspect \"$IMAGE\" > /dev/null 2>&1; then\n183:     echo \"✗ Image not found: $IMAGE\"\n184:     exit 1\n185: fi\n186: echo \"✓ Image exists\"\n187: \n188: # Check image size (< 50MB)\n189: SIZE=$(docker image inspect \"$IMAGE\" --format='{{.Size}}')\n190: SIZE_MB=$((SIZE / 1024 / 1024))\n191: if [ $SIZE_MB -lt 50 ]; then\n192:     echo \"✓ Image size: ${SIZE_MB}MB (< 50MB)\"\n193: else\n194:     echo \"✗ Image size: ${SIZE_MB}MB (>= 50MB)\"\n195:     exit 1\n196: fi\n197: \n198: # Check layer count (<= 5)\n199: LAYERS=$(docker image history \"$IMAGE\" --format='{{.ID}}' | wc -l)\n200: if [ $LAYERS -le 5 ]; then\n201:     echo \"✓ Layer count: $LAYERS (<= 5)\"\n202: else\n203:     echo \"✗ Layer count: $LAYERS (> 5)\"\n204:     exit 1\n205: fi\n206: \n207: # Check non-root user\n208: USER_SPEC=$(docker image inspect \"$IMAGE\" --format='{{.Config.User}}')\n209: if [ -n \"$USER_SPEC\" ] && [ \"$USER_SPEC\" != \"root\" ]; then\n210:     echo \"✓ Running as non-root: $USER_SPEC\"\n211: else\n212:     echo \"✗ Running as root or no user specified\"\n213:     exit 1\n214: fi\n215: \n216: # Check exposed ports\n217: PORTS=$(docker image inspect \"$IMAGE\" --format='{{json .Config.ExposedPorts}}')\n218: if echo \"$PORTS\" | grep -q \"8080\"; then\n219:     echo \"✓ Port 8080 exposed\"\n220: else\n221:     echo \"✗ Port 8080 not exposed\"\n222:     exit 1\n223: fi\n224: \n225: # Check healthcheck\n226: HEALTHCHECK=$(docker image inspect \"$IMAGE\" --format='{{json .Config.Healthcheck}}')\n227: if [ \"$HEALTHCHECK\" != \"null\" ] && [ -n \"$HEALTHCHECK\" ]; then\n228:     echo \"✓ Health check configured\"\n229: else\n230:     echo \"✗ Health check not configured\"\n231:     exit 1\n232: fi\n233: \n234: echo \"\"\n235: echo \"All validations passed!\"\n236: ```\n237: \n238: ### 4. 创建构建测试脚本\n239: \n240: ```bash\n241: #!/bin/bash\n242: # deployment/docker/test/build_test.sh\n243: # Test Docker image build process\n244: \n245: set -e\n246: \n247: echo \"Running Docker build tests...\"\n248: echo \"\"\n249: \n250: # Test 1: Check Dockerfile exists\n251: echo \"Test 1: Checking Dockerfile existence...\"\n252: DOCKERFILES=(\n253:     \"deployment/docker/Dockerfile\"\n254:     \"deployment/docker/Dockerfile.router\"\n255:     \"deployment/docker/Dockerfile.picod\"\n256: )\n257: \n258: for dockerfile in \"${DOCKERFILES[@]}\"; do\n259:     if [ -f \"$dockerfile\" ]; then\n260:         echo \"  ✓ $dockerfile exists\"\n261:     else\n262:         echo \"  ✗ $dockerfile not found\"\n263:         exit 1\n264:     fi\n265: done\n266: \n267: # Test 2: Check Makefile targets\n268: echo \"\"\n269: echo \"Test 2: Checking Makefile targets...\"\n270: if make -n docker-build-all > /dev/null 2>&1; then\n271:     echo \"  ✓ docker-build-all target available\"\n272: else\n273:     echo \"  ✗ docker-build-all target not found\"\n274:     exit 1\n275: fi\n276: \n277: # Test 3: Check Docker daemon\n278: echo \"\"\n279: echo \"Test 3: Checking Docker daemon...\"\n280: if docker info > /dev/null 2>&1; then\n281:     echo \"  ✓ Docker daemon is running\"\n282: else\n283:     echo \"  ✗ Docker daemon is not running\"\n284:     exit 1\n285: fi\n286: \n287: # Test 4: Check buildx availability\n288: echo \"\"\n289: echo \"Test 4: Checking Docker buildx...\"\n290: if docker buildx version > /dev/null 2>&1; then\n291:     echo \"  ✓ Docker buildx is available\"\n292: else\n293:     echo \"  ✗ Docker buildx not found (optional)\"\n294: fi\n295: \n296: echo \"\"\n297: echo \"All build tests passed!\"\n298: ```\n299: \n300: ### 5. 创建运行时测试脚本\n301: \n302: ```bash\n303: #!/bin/bash\n304: # deployment/docker/test/runtime_test.sh\n305: # Test Docker container runtime behavior\n306: \n307: set -e\n308: \n309: echo \"Running Docker runtime tests...\"\n310: echo \"\"\n311: \n312: # Test 1: Container starts successfully\n313: echo \"Test 1: Testing container startup...\"\n314: TEST_IMAGE=\"${TEST_IMAGE:-ghcr.io/volcano-sh/workloadmanager:latest}\"\n315: \n316: CONTAINER_ID=$(docker run -d --rm \"$TEST_IMAGE\" --help 2>/dev/null || true)\n317: if [ -n \"$CONTAINER_ID\" ]; then\n318:     echo \"  ✓ Container started successfully\"\n319:     docker stop \"$CONTAINER_ID\" 2>/dev/null || true\n320: else\n321:     echo \"  ⚠ Container startup test skipped (image may not exist)\"\n322: fi\n323: \n324: # Test 2: Health check configuration\n325: echo \"\"\n326: echo \"Test 2: Checking health check configuration...\"\n327: HEALTHCHECK=$(docker image inspect \"$TEST_IMAGE\" --format='{{json .Config.Healthcheck}}' 2>/dev/null || echo \"null\")\n328: if [ \"$HEALTHCHECK\" != \"null\" ]; then\n329:     echo \"  ✓ Health check is configured\"\n330: else\n331:     echo \"  ⚠ Health check not configured (image may not exist)\"\n332: fi\n333: \n334: # Test 3: Port exposure\n335: echo \"\"\n336: echo \"Test 3: Checking port exposure...\"\n337: PORTS=$(docker image inspect \"$TEST_IMAGE\" --format='{{json .Config.ExposedPorts}}' 2>/dev/null || echo \"null\")\n338: if echo \"$PORTS\" | grep -q \"8080\"; then\n339:     echo \"  ✓ Port 8080 is exposed\"\n340: else\n341:     echo \"  ⚠ Port 8080 not exposed (image may not exist)\"\n342: fi\n343: \n344: # Test 4: Non-root user\n345: echo \"\"\n346: echo \"Test 4: Checking non-root user...\"\n347: USER_SPEC=$(docker image inspect \"$TEST_IMAGE\" --format='{{.Config.User}}' 2>/dev/null || echo \"\")\n348: if [ -n \"$USER_SPEC\" ] && [ \"$USER_SPEC\" != \"root\" ]; then\n349:     echo \"  ✓ Running as non-root: $USER_SPEC\"\n350: else\n351:     echo \"  ⚠ Root user or no user specified (image may not exist)\"\n352: fi\n353: \n354: echo \"\"\n355: echo \"All runtime tests completed!\"\n356: ```\n357: \n358: ### 6. 创建脚本执行权限\n359: \n360: ```bash\n361: chmod +x deployment/docker/test/validate.sh\n362: chmod +x deployment/docker/test/build_test.sh\n363: chmod +x deployment/docker/test/runtime_test.sh\n364: ```\n365: \n366: ### 7. 目录结构\n367: \n368: ```\n369: deployment/docker/test/\n370: ├── validate.sh        # 镜像验证脚本\n371: ├── build_test.sh      # 构建测试脚本\n372: └── runtime_test.sh    # 运行时测试脚本\n373: ```\n374: \n375: ### 8. Makefile 更新（可选增强）\n376: \n377: 如需增强 Makefile，可添加以下目标：\n378: \n379: ```makefile\n380: # 新增：检查依赖\n381: .PHONY: check-docker\n382: check-docker:\n383: \t@command -v docker >/dev/null 2>&1 || { echo \"Docker is required but not installed.\"; exit 1; }\n384: \n385: .PHONY: check-buildx\n386: check-buildx:\n387: \t@docker buildx version >/dev/null 2>&1 || { echo \"Docker buildx is required.\"; exit 1; }\n388: \n389: # 新增：预检查\n390: .PHONY: prereqs\n391: prereqs: check-docker\n392: \t@echo \"✓ All prerequisites met\"\n393: \n394: # 新增：完整 CI 流程\n395: .PHONY: ci\n396: ci: prereqs docker-test docker-build-all docker-validate\n397: \t@echo \"✓ CI pipeline completed\"\n398: ```\n399: \n400: ## Impact Analysis\n401: \n402: ### 依赖影响\n403: \n404: | 依赖项 | 版本 | 用途 |\n405: |--------|------|------|\n406: | GNU Make | ≥3.81 | 构建自动化 |\n407: | Docker | ≥20.10 | 镜像构建和运行 |\n408: | Docker Buildx | ≥0.6 | 多架构构建（可选） |\n409: | Kind | ≥0.11 | 本地 Kubernetes 集群（可选） |\n410: | Bash | ≥4.0 | 脚本执行 |\n411: | Git | 任意 | 版本信息获取 |\n412: \n413: ### 模块依赖关系\n414: \n415: ```\n416: Makefile (根目录)\n417: ├── deployment/docker/Dockerfile           # Workload Manager Dockerfile (AR-032)\n418: ├── deployment/docker/Dockerfile.router    # Router Dockerfile (AR-032)\n419: ├── deployment/docker/Dockerfile.picod     # Picod Dockerfile (AR-032)\n420: ├── deployment/docker/test/validate.sh     # 镜像验证脚本 (本 AR 新增)\n421: ├── deployment/docker/test/build_test.sh   # 构建测试脚本 (本 AR 新增)\n422: └── deployment/docker/test/runtime_test.sh # 运行时测试脚本 (本 AR 新增)\n423: ```\n424: \n425: ### 向后兼容性\n426: \n427: - 现有 Makefile 目标保持不变\n428: - 新增脚本文件不影响现有功能\n429: - 环境变量使用默认值，向后兼容\n430: \n431: ### 测试影响\n432: \n433: - 需要验证 Makefile 目标可正常执行\n434: - 需要验证脚本文件有执行权限\n435: - 需要验证测试脚本在 Docker 缺失时优雅降级\n436: \n437: ## Alternatives Considered\n438: \n439: ### 方案 1: 使用 Task (taskfile.dev) 替代 Make\n440: \n441: **优点:**\n442: - 更现代的语法，支持 YAML\n443: - 跨平台兼容性更好\n444: - 支持任务依赖和并行执行\n445: \n446: **缺点:**\n447: - 需要额外安装 Task 工具\n448: - 增加学习成本\n449: - Make 在项目中的使用已经很普遍\n450: \n451: **决策:** 继续使用 Makefile，保持简单和普遍兼容性。\n452: \n453: ### 方案 2: 使用 Shell 脚本替代 Makefile\n454: \n455: **优点:**\n456: - 更灵活，支持复杂逻辑\n457: - 无需学习 Make 语法\n458: \n459: **缺点:**\n460: - 缺少目标依赖管理\n461: - 并行执行能力弱\n462: - 不适合管理大量相关命令\n463: \n464: **决策:** Makefile 更适合管理构建目标体系。\n465: \n466: ### 方案 3: 每个组件独立 Makefile\n467: \n468: **优点:**\n469: - 组件解耦\n470: - 各自维护构建逻辑\n471: \n472: **缺点:**\n473: - 重复配置（变量、公共目标）\n474: - 全量构建需要多次调用\n475: - 增加维护成本\n476: \n477: **决策:** 使用根目录统一 Makefile，通过目标前缀区分组件。\n478: \n479: ### 方案 4: 完全依赖 CI/CD（本地无构建）\n480: \n481: **优点:**\n482: - 本地环境简化\n483: - 构建一致性高\n484: \n485: **缺点:**\n486: - 开发调试效率低\n487: - 依赖网络和服务可用性\n488: \n489: **决策:** 保留本地构建能力，CI/CD 作为补充。\n490: \n491: ## Testing Strategy\n492: \n493: ### Makefile 目标测试\n494: \n495: 1. **目标可用性测试** - 验证所有 `make` 目标可被调用\n496: 2. **依赖关系测试** - 验证目标依赖正确（如 `docker-build-all` 依赖各组件构建）\n497: 3. **变量覆盖测试** - 验证环境变量可正确覆盖默认值\n498: \n499: ### 脚本测试\n500: \n501: 1. **验证脚本测试** - 对合法镜像验证通过，对非法镜像验证失败\n502: 2. **构建测试** - 验证 Dockerfile、Docker daemon、buildx 检测有效\n503: 3. **运行时测试** - 验证容器启动、健康检查、端口检测有效\n504: \n505: ### 集成测试\n506: \n507: 1. **完整流程测试** - `make docker-build-all` → `make docker-validate` → `make kind-load-all`\n508: 2. **错误处理测试** - Docker 未运行时给出友好提示\n509: 3. **清理测试** - `make docker-clean` 正确清理镜像\n510: \n511: ### 测试覆盖目标\n512: \n513: - Makefile 目标：100%（所有目标可执行）\n514: - 验证脚本：100%（所有检查项有效）\n515: - 构建测试：100%（所有前置检查有效）\n516: - 运行时测试：100%（所有运行时检查有效）\n517: \n518: ## Acceptance Criteria\n519: \n520: - [ ] Makefile 所有目标可正常执行 (`make help` 列出所有目标)\n521: - [ ] `make docker-build-all` 成功构建三个镜像\n522: - [ ] `make docker-push-all` 成功推送镜像（需有推送权限）\n523: - [ ] `make kind-load-all` 成功加载镜像到 Kind 集群\n524: - [ ] `make docker-validate` 成功验证镜像\n525: - [ ] `make docker-test` 成功运行所有测试\n526: - [ ] `make docker-clean` 成功清理本地镜像\n527: - [ ] `make docker-buildx-all` 成功构建多架构镜像（需 buildx）\n528: - [ ] 验证脚本 (`validate.sh`) 可独立执行\n529: - [ ] 构建测试脚本 (`build_test.sh`) 可独立执行\n530: - [ ] 运行时测试脚本 (`runtime_test.sh`) 可独立执行\n531: - [ ] 所有脚本具有执行权限\n532: - [ ] 文档完整（帮助信息、使用说明）\n533: \n534: ## Dependencies\n535: \n536: ### 必需依赖\n537: - GNU Make ≥3.81\n538: - Docker ≥20.10\n539: - Bash ≥4.0\n540: - Git\n541: \n542: ### 可选依赖\n543: - Docker Buildx ≥0.6（多架构构建）\n544: - Kind ≥0.11（本地 Kubernetes 测试）\n545: \n546: ### 被依赖\n547: - AR-032 (Dockerfile 多阶段构建) - 提供 Dockerfile\n548: - AR-030 (Helm Chart) - 镜像用于 Helm 部署\n549: \n550: ## Migration Notes\n551: \n552: ### 从现有 Makefile 迁移\n553: \n554: 当前 Makefile 已经是最新状态，无需迁移。新增的脚本文件是 Makefile 目标的依赖，需要创建。\n555: \n556: ### 破坏性变更\n557: 无 - 仅补充缺失的脚本文件。\n558: \n559: ### 行为变更\n560: - `make docker-validate` 从失败变为成功（验证脚本存在后）\n561: - `make docker-test` 从失败变为成功（测试脚本存在后）\n562: \n563: ## Open Questions\n564: \n565: 1. 是否需要支持 Windows 环境下的 Makefile 等价物（如 PowerShell 脚本）？\n566: 2. 是否需要集成镜像签名（cosign）到 Makefile 目标？\n567: 3. 是否需要支持远程 Docker daemon（DOCKER_HOST 环境变量）？\n568: \n569: ## References\n570: \n571: - `Makefile` - 现有 Makefile 文件\n572: - `changes/AR-032/proposal.md` - Dockerfile 多阶段构建提案\n573: - `deployment/docker/Dockerfile` - Workload Manager Dockerfile\n574: - `deployment/docker/Dockerfile.router` - Router Dockerfile\n575: - `deployment/docker/Dockerfile.picod` - Picod Dockerfile\n576: - GNU Make Best Practices: https://www.gnu.org/software/make/manual/make.html\n577: - Docker Makefile Best Practices: https://docs.docker.com/build/building/best-practices/\n\n(End of file - total 577 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-033: Makefile 构建目标体系\n\n## Purpose\n\n本提案实现 AgentCube 项目的 Makefile 构建目标体系，为 Docker 镜像构建、推送、验证、测试提供标准化的自动化命令。该 Makefile 是 AgentCube 容器化工作流的核心入口，支撑开发、CI/CD、生产环境的镜像生命周期管理。\n\n目标是：\n\n1. **构建自动化** - 提供统一的 `make` 命令简化 Docker 镜像构建流程，减少手动操作错误\n2. **目标分层** - 支持全量构建 (`docker-build-all`) 和单组件构建 (`docker-build-workloadmanager` 等)，适应不同场景\n3. **推送标准化** - 统一镜像推送流程，自动关联 VERSION、COMMIT_SHA、DOCKER_TAG 多标签\n4. **集群集成** - 提供 Kind 集群加载目标 (`kind-load-all`)，支持本地开发测试\n5. **多架构支持** - 集成 Docker Buildx，支持 amd64、arm64 多架构镜像构建\n6. **质量门禁** - 内置镜像验证 (`docker-validate`) 和测试 (`docker-test`) 目标，确保镜像质量\n7. **清理工具** - 提供本地镜像清理目标 (`docker-clean`)，减少磁盘占用\n\n本提案基于 existing Makefile (仅包含 Docker 相关目标) 进行扩展，遵循 Makefile 最佳实践和 AR-032 Dockerfile 多阶段构建规范。\n\n## Scope\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-033/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775882670404,"end":1775882670415}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775882670423,"sessionID":"ses_285255de5ffes5chFbBEceByDE","part":{"id":"prt_d7adb01f7001vi9u6QZZRnjTpx","messageID":"msg_d7adaf800001QIMczXcRjv36XB","sessionID":"ses_285255de5ffes5chFbBEceByDE","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_22305ef9f71847b7b005ca2b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-033/spec/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-033/spec/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Specification — AR-033: Makefile 构建目标体系\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **Module:** `root`  \n6: **Language:** Makefile  \n7: **Size:** M  \n8: **Type:** Makefile target system for Docker image build, push, validate, test lifecycle management\n9: \n10: **Base Specs:** design.md, deployment/docker/delta-spec.md (AR-032)\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Requirements & Scenarios\n15: \n16: ### REQ-033.1: Build Targets (docker-build-*)\n17: \n18: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide Make targets for building Docker images for all components (Workload Manager, Router, Picod).\n19: \n20: #### Scenario: Build all images\n21: - **GIVEN** Makefile exists with `docker-build-all` target\n22: - **WHEN** `make docker-build-all` is executed\n23: - **THEN** it SHALL build all three images (workloadmanager, router, picod) sequentially\n24: \n25: #### Scenario: Build Workload Manager image\n26: - **GIVEN** `deployment/docker/Dockerfile` exists\n27: - **WHEN** `make docker-build-workloadmanager` is executed\n28: - **THEN** it SHALL build image tagged with `$(DOCKER_TAG)`, `$(COMMIT_SHA)`, and `$(VERSION)`\n29: \n30: #### Scenario: Build Router image\n31: - **GIVEN** `deployment/docker/Dockerfile.router` exists\n32: - **WHEN** `make docker-build-router` is executed\n33: - **THEN** it SHALL build image tagged with `$(DOCKER_TAG)`, `$(COMMIT_SHA)`, and `$(VERSION)`\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Build Picod image\n36: - **GIVEN** `deployment/docker/Dockerfile.picod` exists\n37: - **WHEN** `make docker-build-picod` is executed\n38: - **THEN** it SHALL build image tagged with `$(DOCKER_TAG)`, `$(COMMIT_SHA)`, and `$(VERSION)`\n39: \n40: #### Scenario: Default registry configuration\n41: - **GIVEN** no `DOCKER_REGISTRY` variable is set\n42: - **WHEN** any build target runs\n43: - **THEN** it SHALL use default registry `ghcr.io/volcano-sh`\n44: \n45: #### Scenario: Custom registry override\n46: - **GIVEN** `DOCKER_REGISTRY=registry.example.com` is set\n47: - **WHEN** build target runs\n48: - **THEN** it SHALL use custom registry in image name\n49: \n50: #### Scenario: Default tag configuration\n51: - **GIVEN** no `DOCKER_TAG` variable is set\n52: - **WHEN** any build target runs\n53: - **THEN** it SHALL use default tag `latest`\n54: \n55: #### Scenario: Custom tag override\n56: - **GIVEN** `DOCKER_TAG=v1.0.0` is set\n57: - **WHEN** build target runs\n58: - **THEN** it SHALL use custom tag in image name\n59: \n60: ---\n61: \n62: ### REQ-033.2: Push Targets (docker-push-*)\n63: \n64: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide Make targets for pushing Docker images to container registry.\n65: \n66: #### Scenario: Push all images\n67: - **GIVEN** images are built and `docker-push-all` target exists\n68: - **WHEN** `make docker-push-all` is executed\n69: - **THEN** it SHALL push all three images to registry\n70: \n71: #### Scenario: Push Workload Manager image\n72: - **GIVEN** workloadmanager image is built\n73: - **WHEN** `make docker-push-workloadmanager` is executed\n74: - **THEN** it SHALL push all three tags (latest, commit-sha, version) to registry\n75: \n76: #### Scenario: Push Router image\n77: - **GIVEN** router image is built\n78: - **WHEN** `make docker-push-router` is executed\n79: - **THEN** it SHALL push all three tags (latest, commit-sha, version) to registry\n80: \n81: #### Scenario: Push Picod image\n82: - **GIVEN** picod image is built\n83: - **WHEN** `make docker-push-picod` is executed\n84: - **THEN** it SHALL push all three tags (latest, commit-sha, version) to registry\n85: \n86: #### Scenario: Push with custom registry\n87: - **GIVEN** `DOCKER_REGISTRY=registry.example.com` is set\n88: - **WHEN** push target runs\n89: - **THEN** it SHALL push to specified custom registry\n90: \n91: ---\n92: \n93: ### REQ-033.3: Kind Load Targets (kind-load-*)\n94: \n95: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide Make targets for loading Docker images to local Kind Kubernetes cluster.\n96: \n97: #### Scenario: Load all images to Kind\n98: - **GIVEN** Kind cluster is running and images are built\n99: - **WHEN** `make kind-load-all` is executed\n100: - **THEN** it SHALL load all three images to Kind cluster\n101: \n102: #### Scenario: Load Workload Manager image to Kind\n103: - **GIVEN** Kind cluster is running and workloadmanager image is built\n104: - **WHEN** `make kind-load-workloadmanager` is executed\n105: - **THEN** it SHALL load workloadmanager image with `$(DOCKER_TAG)` to Kind\n106: \n107: #### Scenario: Load Router image to Kind\n108: - **GIVEN** Kind cluster is running and router image is built\n109: - **WHEN** `make kind-load-router` is executed\n110: - **THEN** it SHALL load router image with `$(DOCKER_TAG)` to Kind\n111: \n112: #### Scenario: Load Picod image to Kind\n113: - **GIVEN** Kind cluster is running and picod image is built\n114: - **WHEN** `make kind-load-picod` is executed\n115: - **THEN** it SHALL load picod image with `$(DOCKER_TAG)` to Kind\n116: \n117: #### Scenario: Kind not installed\n118: - **GIVEN** Kind is not installed on the system\n119: - **WHEN** `make kind-load-all` is executed\n120: - **THEN** it SHALL fail with appropriate error message about Kind not found\n121: \n122: ---\n123: \n124: ### REQ-033.4: Multi-architecture Build Targets (docker-buildx-*)\n125: \n126: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide Make targets for building multi-architecture Docker images using Docker Buildx.\n127: \n128: #### Scenario: Build all multi-arch images\n129: - **GIVEN** Docker Buildx is available and `docker-buildx-all` target exists\n130: - **WHEN** `make docker-buildx-all` is executed\n131: - **THEN** it SHALL build multi-arch images for all three components\n132: \n133: #### Scenario: Build Workload Manager multi-arch image\n134: - **GIVEN** Docker Buildx is available\n135: - **WHEN** `make docker-buildx-workloadmanager` is executed\n136: - **THEN** it SHALL build image for `linux/amd64,linux/arm64` platforms and push to registry\n137: \n138: #### Scenario: Build Router multi-arch image\n139: - **GIVEN** Docker Buildx is available\n140: - **WHEN** `make docker-buildx-router` is executed\n141: - **THEN** it SHALL build image for `linux/amd64,linux/arm64` platforms and push to registry\n142: \n143: #### Scenario: Build Picod multi-arch image\n144: - **GIVEN** Docker Buildx is available\n145: - **WHEN** `make docker-buildx-picod` is executed\n146: - **THEN** it SHALL build image for `linux/amd64,linux/arm64` platforms and push to registry\n147: \n148: #### Scenario: Buildx not available\n149: - **GIVEN** Docker Buildx is not installed\n150: - **WHEN** `make docker-buildx-all` is executed\n151: - **THEN** it SHALL fail with appropriate error message about buildx not found\n152: \n153: ---\n154: \n155: ### REQ-033.5: Validate Targets (docker-validate-*)\n156: \n157: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide Make targets for validating Docker images against quality standards (size, layers, security, ports).\n158: \n159: #### Scenario: Validate all images\n160: - **GIVEN** images are built and `docker-validate` target exists\n161: - **WHEN** `make docker-validate` is executed\n162: - **THEN** it SHALL run validation script against all three images\n163: \n164: #### Scenario: Validate Workload Manager image\n165: - **GIVEN** workloadmanager image is built\n166: - **WHEN** `make docker-validate-workloadmanager` is executed\n167: - **THEN** it SHALL run `deployment/docker/test/validate.sh` against the image\n168: \n169: #### Scenario: Validate Router image\n170: - **GIVEN** router image is built\n171: - **WHEN** `make docker-validate-router` is executed\n172: - **THEN** it SHALL run `deployment/docker/test/validate.sh` against the image\n173: \n174: #### Scenario: Validate Picod image\n175: - **GIVEN** picod image is built\n176: - **WHEN** `make docker-validate-picod` is executed\n177: - **THEN** it SHALL run `deployment/docker/test/validate.sh` against the image\n178: \n179: #### Scenario: Validation script not found\n180: - **GIVEN** `deployment/docker/test/validate.sh` does not exist\n181: - **WHEN** `make docker-validate` is executed\n182: - **THEN** it SHALL fail with appropriate error message about missing script\n183: \n184: ---\n185: \n186: ### REQ-033.6: Test Targets (docker-test-*)\n187: \n188: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide Make targets for running Docker build and runtime tests.\n189: \n190: #### Scenario: Run all Docker tests\n191: - **GIVEN** `docker-test` target exists\n192: - **WHEN** `make docker-test` is executed\n193: - **THEN** it SHALL run both `docker-test-build` and `docker-test-runtime`\n194: \n195: #### Scenario: Run build tests\n196: - **GIVEN** `docker-test-build` target exists\n197: - **WHEN** `make docker-test-build` is executed\n198: - **THEN** it SHALL run `deployment/docker/test/build_test.sh`\n199: \n200: #### Scenario: Run runtime tests\n201: - **GIVEN** `docker-test-runtime` target exists\n202: - **WHEN** `make docker-test-runtime` is executed\n203: - **THEN** it SHALL run `deployment/docker/test/runtime_test.sh`\n204: \n205: #### Scenario: Test script not found\n206: - **GIVEN** test script does not exist\n207: - **WHEN** corresponding test target is executed\n208: - **THEN** it SHALL fail with appropriate error message about missing script\n209: \n210: ---\n211: \n212: ### REQ-033.7: Clean Target (docker-clean)\n213: \n214: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide Make target for cleaning up local Docker images.\n215: \n216: #### Scenario: Clean all local images\n217: - **GIVEN** local images exist and `docker-clean` target exists\n218: - **WHEN** `make docker-clean` is executed\n219: - **THEN** it SHALL remove all local tags for workloadmanager, router, and picod images\n220: \n221: #### Scenario: Clean with missing images\n222: - **GIVEN** some images do not exist locally\n223: - **WHEN** `make docker-clean` is executed\n224: - **THEN** it SHALL NOT fail and SHALL silently skip missing images\n225: \n226: ---\n227: \n228: ### REQ-033.8: Help Target (help)\n229: \n230: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a `help` target that prints available Make targets and their descriptions.\n231: \n232: #### Scenario: Display help information\n233: - **GIVEN** `help` target exists in Makefile\n234: - **WHEN** `make help` is executed\n235: - **THEN** it SHALL print all available targets grouped by category (build, push, kind, buildx, test, validate, clean)\n236: \n237: #### Scenario: Display variable values\n238: - **GIVEN** `help` target is executed\n239: - **WHEN** help output is printed\n240: - **THEN** it SHALL show current values of `DOCKER_REGISTRY`, `DOCKER_TAG`, `VERSION`, and `COMMIT_SHA`\n241: \n242: ---\n243: \n244: ### REQ-033.9: Validation Script (validate.sh)\n245: \n246: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide `deployment/docker/test/validate.sh` script for validating Docker images.\n247: \n248: #### Scenario: Validate image size\n249: - **GIVEN** a Docker image exists\n250: - **WHEN** `validate.sh` runs against the image\n251: - **THEN** it SHALL check that image size is under 50MB\n252: \n253: #### Scenario: Validate layer count\n254: - **GIVEN** a Docker image exists\n255: - **WHEN** `validate.sh` runs\n256: - **THEN** it SHALL check that image has 5 or fewer layers\n257: \n258: #### Scenario: Validate non-root user\n259: - **GIVEN** a Docker image exists\n260: - **WHEN** `validate.sh` runs\n261: - **THEN** it SHALL check that image specifies non-root user (not root)\n262: \n263: #### Scenario: Validate port exposure\n264: - **GIVEN** a Docker image exists\n265: - **WHEN** `validate.sh` runs\n266: - **THEN** it SHALL check that port 8080 is exposed\n267: \n268: #### Scenario: Validate health check\n269: - **GIVEN** a Docker image exists\n270: - **WHEN** `validate.sh` runs\n271: - **THEN** it SHALL check that HEALTHCHECK instruction is configured\n272: \n273: #### Scenario: Image not found\n274: - **GIVEN** the specified image does not exist\n275: - **WHEN** `validate.sh` is executed\n276: - **THEN** it SHALL exit with error code and message \"Image not found\"\n277: \n278: #### Scenario: Script is executable\n279: - **GIVEN** `validate.sh` file exists\n280: - **WHEN** file permissions are checked\n281: - **THEN** it SHALL have execute permission (`chmod +x`)\n282: \n283: ---\n284: \n285: ### REQ-033.10: Build Test Script (build_test.sh)\n286: \n287: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide `deployment/docker/test/build_test.sh` script for testing Docker build process.\n288: \n289: #### Scenario: Check Dockerfile existence\n290: - **GIVEN** `build_test.sh` runs\n291: - **WHEN** it checks for Dockerfiles\n292: - **THEN** it SHALL verify `Dockerfile`, `Dockerfile.router`, and `Dockerfile.picod` exist\n293: \n294: #### Scenario: Check Makefile targets\n295: - **GIVEN** `build_test.sh` runs\n296: - **WHEN** it checks Makefile targets\n297: - **THEN** it SHALL verify `docker-build-all` target is available\n298: \n299: #### Scenario: Check Docker daemon\n300: - **GIVEN** `build_test.sh` runs\n301: - **WHEN** it checks Docker daemon\n302: - **THEN** it SHALL verify Docker daemon is running\n303: \n304: #### Scenario: Check buildx availability\n305: - **GIVEN** `build_test.sh` runs\n306: - **WHEN** it checks buildx\n307: - **THEN** it SHALL verify Docker buildx is available (optional, non-fatal)\n308: \n309: #### Scenario: Script is executable\n310: - **GIVEN** `build_test.sh` file exists\n311: - **WHEN** file permissions are checked\n312: - **THEN** it SHALL have execute permission (`chmod +x`)\n313: \n314: ---\n315: \n316: ### REQ-033.11: Runtime Test Script (runtime_test.sh)\n317: \n318: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide `deployment/docker/test/runtime_test.sh` script for testing Docker container runtime behavior.\n319: \n320: #### Scenario: Test container startup\n321: - **GIVEN** `runtime_test.sh` runs and test image exists\n322: - **WHEN** it attempts container startup\n323: - **THEN** it SHALL verify container starts successfully\n324: \n325: #### Scenario: Test health check configuration\n326: - **GIVEN** `runtime_test.sh` runs\n327: - **WHEN** it checks health check\n328: - **THEN** it SHALL verify HEALTHCHECK is configured in image\n329: \n330: #### Scenario: Test port exposure\n331: - **GIVEN** `runtime_test.sh` runs\n332: - **WHEN** it checks ports\n333: - **THEN** it SHALL verify port 8080 is exposed\n334: \n335: #### Scenario: Test non-root user\n336: - **GIVEN** `runtime_test.sh` runs\n337: - **WHEN** it checks user configuration\n338: - **THEN** it SHALL verify container runs as non-root user\n339: \n340: #### Scenario: Image not available\n341: - **GIVEN** test image does not exist locally\n342: - **WHEN** `runtime_test.sh` runs\n343: - **THEN** it SHALL gracefully skip tests with warning messages (non-fatal)\n344: \n345: #### Scenario: Script is executable\n346: - **GIVEN** `runtime_test.sh` file exists\n347: - **WHEN** file permissions are checked\n348: - **THEN** it SHALL have execute permission (`chmod +x`)\n349: \n350: ---\n351: \n352: ### REQ-033.12: Version and Commit Variables\n353: \n354: **Requirement:** The system SHALL automatically derive VERSION and COMMIT_SHA from git for use in image tagging.\n355: \n356: #### Scenario: Derive VERSION from git tags\n357: - **GIVEN** repository has git tags\n358: - **WHEN** Makefile evaluates `VERSION` variable\n359: - **THEN** it SHALL use `git describe --tags --always --dirty` output\n360: \n361: #### Scenario: Fallback VERSION for no tags\n362: - **GIVEN** repository has no git tags\n363: - **WHEN** Makefile evaluates `VERSION` variable\n364: - **THEN** it SHALL fallback to `dev`\n365: \n366: #### Scenario: Derive COMMIT_SHA from git\n367: - **GIVEN** repository is a valid git repo\n368: - **WHEN** Makefile evaluates `COMMIT_SHA` variable\n369: - **THEN** it SHALL use `git rev-parse --short HEAD` output\n370: \n371: #### Scenario: Fallback COMMIT_SHA for non-git\n372: - **GIVEN** not in a git repository\n373: - **WHEN** Makefile evaluates `COMMIT_SHA` variable\n374: - **THEN** it SHALL fallback to `unknown`\n375: \n376: #### Scenario: Override VERSION from environment\n377: - **GIVEN** `VERSION` environment variable is set\n378: - **WHEN** Makefile is invoked\n379: - **THEN** it SHALL use environment variable value\n380: \n381: #### Scenario: Override COMMIT_SHA from environment\n382: - **GIVEN** `COMMIT_SHA` environment variable is set\n383: - **WHEN** Makefile is invoked\n384: - **THEN** it SHALL use environment variable value\n385: \n386: ---\n387: \n388: ### REQ-033.13: Image Name Configuration\n389: \n390: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide consistent image naming convention for all components.\n391: \n392: #### Scenario: Workload Manager image name\n393: - **GIVEN** Makefile is evaluated\n394: - **WHEN** `WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE` variable is expanded\n395: - **THEN** it SHALL equal `$(DOCKER_REGISTRY)/workloadmanager`\n396: \n397: #### Scenario: Router image name\n398: - **GIVEN** Makefile is evaluated\n399: - **WHEN** `ROUTER_IMAGE` variable is expanded\n400: - **THEN** it SHALL equal `$(DOCKER_REGISTRY)/router`\n401: \n402: #### Scenario: Picod image name\n403: - **GIVEN** Makefile is evaluated\n404: - **WHEN** `PICOD_IMAGE` variable is expanded\n405: - **THEN** it SHALL equal `$(DOCKER_REGISTRY)/picod`\n406: \n407: ---\n408: \n409: ### REQ-033.14: PHONY Target Declarations\n410: \n411: **Requirement:** The system SHALL declare all Make targets as `.PHONY` to prevent conflicts with files of the same name.\n412: \n413: #### Scenario: All targets declared as PHONY\n414: - **GIVEN** Makefile exists\n415: - **WHEN** `.PHONY` declarations are inspected\n416: - **THEN** all targets (docker-build-*, docker-push-*, kind-load-*, docker-buildx-*, docker-validate-*, docker-test-*, docker-clean, help) SHALL be declared as `.PHONY`\n417: \n418: ---\n419: \n420: ### REQ-033.15: Error Handling\n421: \n422: **Requirement:** The system SHALL handle errors gracefully in Make targets and scripts.\n423: \n424: #### Scenario: Docker command failure\n425: - **GIVEN** Docker daemon is not running\n426: - **WHEN** a build target is executed\n427: - **THEN** it SHALL fail with clear error message about Docker not being available\n428: \n429: #### Scenario: Clean target with missing images\n430: - **GIVEN** some images do not exist\n431: - **WHEN** `make docker-clean` runs\n432: - **THEN** it SHALL NOT fail (uses `-` prefix to ignore errors)\n433: \n434: #### Scenario: Missing Dockerfile\n435: - **GIVEN** Dockerfile does not exist\n436: - **WHEN** build target runs\n437: - **THEN** Docker build command SHALL fail with appropriate error\n438: \n439: ---\n440: \n441: ## Data Types\n442: \n443: ```makefile\n444: # Makefile variables\n445: DOCKER_REGISTRY := ghcr.io/volcano-sh     # Default container registry\n446: DOCKER_TAG := latest                       # Default image tag\n447: VERSION := $(shell git describe --tags --always --dirty 2>/dev/null || echo \"dev\")\n448: COMMIT_SHA := $(shell git rev-parse --short HEAD 2>/dev/null || echo \"unknown\")\n449: \n450: # Image names (constructed)\n451: WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE := $(DOCKER_REGISTRY)/workloadmanager\n452: ROUTER_IMAGE := $(DOCKER_REGISTRY)/router\n453: PICOD_IMAGE := $(DOCKER_REGISTRY)/picod\n454: ```\n455: \n456: ---\n457: \n458: ## File Structure\n459: \n460: ```\n461: project-root/\n462: ├── Makefile                              # Main Makefile with all targets\n463: ├── deployment/\n464: │   └── docker/\n465: │       ├── Dockerfile                    # Workload Manager Dockerfile (AR-032)\n466: │       ├── Dockerfile.router             # Router Dockerfile (AR-032)\n467: │       ├── Dockerfile.picod              # Picod Dockerfile (AR-032)\n468: │       └── test/\n469: │           ├── validate.sh               # Image validation script (new)\n470: │           ├── build_test.sh             # Build test script (new)\n471: │           └── runtime_test.sh           # Runtime test script (new)\n472: ```\n473: \n474: ---\n475: \n476: ## Make Targets\n477: \n478: | Target | Category | Description |\n479: |--------|----------|-------------|\n480: | `docker-build-all` | Build | Build all three Docker images |\n481: | `docker-build-workloadmanager` | Build | Build Workload Manager image |\n482: | `docker-build-router` | Build | Build Router image |\n483: | `docker-build-picod` | Build | Build Picod image |\n484: | `docker-push-all` | Push | Push all images to registry |\n485: | `docker-push-workloadmanager` | Push | Push Workload Manager image |\n486: | `docker-push-router` | Push | Push Router image |\n487: | `docker-push-picod` | Push | Push Picod image |\n488: | `kind-load-all` | Kind | Load all images to Kind cluster |\n489: | `kind-load-workloadmanager` | Kind | Load Workload Manager image to Kind |\n490: | `kind-load-router` | Kind | Load Router image to Kind |\n491: | `kind-load-picod` | Kind | Load Picod image to Kind |\n492: | `docker-buildx-all` | Buildx | Build multi-arch images (amd64, arm64) |\n493: | `docker-buildx-workloadmanager` | Buildx | Build multi-arch Workload Manager |\n494: | `docker-buildx-router` | Buildx | Build multi-arch Router |\n495: | `docker-buildx-picod` | Buildx | Build multi-arch Picod |\n496: | `docker-validate` | Validate | Validate all images |\n497: | `docker-validate-workloadmanager` | Validate | Validate Workload Manager image |\n498: | `docker-validate-router` | Validate | Validate Router image |\n499: | `docker-validate-picod` | Validate | Validate Picod image |\n500: | `docker-test` | Test | Run all Docker tests |\n501: | `docker-test-build` | Test | Run build tests |\n502: | `docker-test-runtime` | Test | Run runtime tests |\n503: | `docker-clean` | Clean | Clean up local images |\n504: | `help` | Help | Print available targets and variables |\n505: \n506: ---\n507: \n508: ## Environment Variables\n509: \n510: | Variable | Purpose | Default | Overridable |\n511: |----------|---------|---------|-------------|\n512: | `DOCKER_REGISTRY` | Container registry URL | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh` | Yes |\n513: | `DOCKER_TAG` | Default image tag | `latest` | Yes |\n514: | `VERSION` | Git-derived version | `git describe` or `dev` | Yes |\n515: | `COMMIT_SHA` | Git commit short hash | `git rev-parse` or `unknown` | Yes |\n516: | `TEST_IMAGE` | Test image for runtime tests | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh/workloadmanager:latest` | Yes |\n517: \n518: ---\n519: \n520: ## Script Interfaces\n521: \n522: ### validate.sh\n523: \n524: ```bash\n525: # Usage\n526: ./deployment/docker/test/validate.sh <image-name>\n527: \n528: # Exit codes\n529: 0 - All validations passed\n530: 1 - Validation failed or image not found\n531: \n532: # Validations performed\n533: - Image existence check\n534: - Image size < 50MB\n535: - Layer count <= 5\n536: - Non-root user specified\n537: - Port 8080 exposed\n538: - Health check configured\n539: ```\n540: \n541: ### build_test.sh\n542: \n543: ```bash\n544: # Usage\n545: ./deployment/docker/test/build_test.sh\n546: \n547: # Exit codes\n548: 0 - All build tests passed\n549: 1 - Test failed\n550: \n551: # Tests performed\n552: - Dockerfile existence check (3 files)\n553: - Makefile target availability\n554: - Docker daemon running check\n555: - Docker buildx availability (optional)\n556: ```\n557: \n558: ### runtime_test.sh\n559: \n560: ```bash\n561: # Usage\n562: ./deployment/docker/test/runtime_test.sh\n563: \n564: # Exit codes\n565: 0 - All runtime tests completed\n566: 1 - Critical test failed\n567: \n568: # Tests performed\n569: - Container startup test\n570: - Health check configuration check\n571: - Port exposure check\n572: - Non-root user check\n573: ```\n574: \n575: ---\n576: \n577: ## Acceptance Checklist\n578: \n579: - [ ] `Makefile` — Contains all build, push, kind, buildx, validate, test, clean, and help targets\n580: - [ ] `Makefile` — All targets declared as `.PHONY`\n581: - [ ] `Makefile` — Variables `DOCKER_REGISTRY`, `DOCKER_TAG`, `VERSION`, `COMMIT_SHA` defined\n582: - [ ] `Makefile` — Image name variables for all three components\n583: - [ ] `make help` — Prints all available targets and current variable values\n584: - [ ] `make docker-build-all` — Builds all three images successfully\n585: - [ ] `make docker-push-all` — Pushes all images (with valid credentials)\n586: - [ ] `make kind-load-all` — Loads images to Kind cluster (with Kind installed)\n587: - [ ] `make docker-buildx-all` — Builds multi-arch images (with buildx available)\n588: - [ ] `make docker-validate` — Validates all images\n589: - [ ] `make docker-test` — Runs all tests\n590: - [ ] `make docker-clean` — Cleans up local images\n591: - [ ] `deployment/docker/test/validate.sh` — Exists and is executable\n592: - [ ] `deployment/docker/test/build_test.sh` — Exists and is executable\n593: - [ ] `deployment/docker/test/runtime_test.sh` — Exists and is executable\n594: - [ ] `validate.sh` — Checks image size, layers, user, ports, healthcheck\n595: - [ ] `build_test.sh` — Checks Dockerfiles, Makefile targets, Docker daemon\n596: - [ ] `runtime_test.sh` — Tests container runtime behavior\n597: - [ ] VERSION variable — Derived from git tags with fallback to `dev`\n598: - [ ] COMMIT_SHA variable — Derived from git with fallback to `unknown`\n599: - [ ] Variables overridable — Can be set from environment or command line\n600: - [ ] Error handling — Clean target ignores missing images gracefully\n601: \n602: ---\n603: \n604: ## Open Questions\n605: \n606: 1. Should Windows support be added via PowerShell scripts or WSL-only?\n607: 2. Should cosign image signing be integrated into push targets?\n608: 3. Should remote Docker daemon support (DOCKER_HOST) be explicitly documented?\n609: 4. Should additional validation checks be added (e.g., vulnerability scanning with Trivy)?\n610: 5. Should a `make ci` target be added that chains test → build → validate?\n\n(End of file - total 610 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Specification — AR-033: Makefile 构建目标体系\n\n## Overview\n\n**Module:** `root`  \n**Language:** Makefile  \n**Size:** M  \n**Type:** Makefile target system for Docker image build, push, validate, test lifecycle management\n\n**Base Specs:** design.md, deployment/docker/delta-spec.md (AR-032)\n\n---\n\n## Requirements & Scenarios\n\n### REQ-033.1: Build Targets (docker-build-*)\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide Make targets for building Docker images for all components (Workload Manager, Router, Picod).\n\n#### Scenario: Build all images","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-033/spec/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775882670399,"end":1775882670421}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775882670426,"sessionID":"ses_285255de5ffes5chFbBEceByDE","part":{"id":"prt_d7adb071c001gKonq7YOpD5i7w","messageID":"msg_d7adaf800001QIMczXcRjv36XB","sessionID":"ses_285255de5ffes5chFbBEceByDE","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_1ede21185f3e42e8a0a64b39","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-033/design/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-033/design/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Design: AR-033 — Makefile 构建目标体系\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This document describes the technical implementation for the Makefile build target system in AgentCube. The Makefile provides a comprehensive set of targets for building, pushing, testing, and managing Docker container images across multiple components (Workload Manager, Router, Picod), with support for multi-architecture builds, Kind cluster integration, and image validation.\n6: \n7: ## Architecture\n8: \n9: ### Component Structure\n10: \n11: ```\n12: root/\n13: ├── Makefile                          # Main build system\n14: ├── deployment/\n15: │   └── docker/\n16: │       ├── Dockerfile                # Workload Manager Dockerfile\n17: │       ├── Dockerfile.router         # Router Dockerfile\n18: │       ├── Dockerfile.picod          # Picod Dockerfile\n19: │       ├── test/\n20: │       │   ├── validate.sh           # Image validation script\n21: │       │   ├── build_test.sh         # Build verification tests\n22: │       │   └── runtime_test.sh       # Runtime verification tests\n23: │       └── validate.sh               # Main validation entry point\n24: └── bin/                              # Build artifacts\n25: ```\n26: \n27: ### Target Categories\n28: \n29: The Makefile organizes targets into logical categories:\n30: \n31: 1. **Build Targets** - `docker-build-*`\n32: 2. **Push Targets** - `docker-push-*`\n33: 3. **Kind Integration** - `kind-load-*`\n34: 4. **Multi-architecture** - `docker-buildx-*`\n35: 5. **Test & Validate** - `docker-test*`, `docker-validate*`\n36: 6. **Cleanup** - `docker-clean`\n37: 7. **Help** - `help`\n38: \n39: ### Integration Points\n40: \n41: - **Docker** - Primary build and runtime engine\n42: - **Docker Buildx** - Multi-architecture builds\n43: - **Kind** - Local Kubernetes testing\n44: - **Git** - Version tagging and commit SHA injection\n45: - **Shell Scripts** - Test and validation automation\n46: \n47: ## Data Structures\n48: \n49: ### Configuration Variables\n50: \n51: ```makefile\n52: # Docker configuration\n53: DOCKER_REGISTRY ?= ghcr.io/volcano-sh\n54: DOCKER_TAG ?= latest\n55: VERSION ?= $(shell git describe --tags --always --dirty 2>/dev/null || echo \"dev\")\n56: COMMIT_SHA ?= $(shell git rev-parse --short HEAD 2>/dev/null || echo \"unknown\")\n57: \n58: # Image names\n59: WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE := $(DOCKER_REGISTRY)/workloadmanager\n60: ROUTER_IMAGE := $(DOCKER_REGISTRY)/router\n61: PICOD_IMAGE := $(DOCKER_REGISTRY)/picod\n62: ```\n63: \n64: ### Image Metadata\n65: \n66: Each Docker image receives the following metadata via build arguments:\n67: \n68: | Variable | Source | Description |\n69: |----------|--------|-------------|\n70: | `VERSION` | `git describe --tags --always --dirty` | Git-based version string |\n71: | `COMMIT_SHA` | `git rev-parse --short HEAD` | Short commit hash |\n72: | `DOCKER_TAG` | Environment or default `latest` | Image tag |\n73: | `DOCKER_REGISTRY` | Environment or default `ghcr.io/volcano-sh` | Container registry |\n74: \n75: ### Target Dependency Graph\n76: \n77: ```\n78: docker-build-all\n79: ├── docker-build-workloadmanager\n80: ├── docker-build-router\n81: └── docker-build-picod\n82: \n83: docker-push-all\n84: ├── docker-push-workloadmanager\n85: ├── docker-push-router\n86: └── docker-push-picod\n87: \n88: kind-load-all\n89: ├── kind-load-workloadmanager\n90: ├── kind-load-router\n91: └── kind-load-picod\n92: \n93: docker-buildx-all\n94: ├── docker-buildx-workloadmanager\n95: ├── docker-buildx-router\n96: └── docker-buildx-picod\n97: \n98: docker-validate\n99: ├── docker-validate-workloadmanager\n100: ├── docker-validate-router\n101: └── docker-validate-picod\n102: \n103: docker-test\n104: ├── docker-test-build\n105: └── docker-test-runtime\n106: \n107: docker-clean (independent)\n108: help (independent)\n109: ```\n110: \n111: ## API Contracts\n112: \n113: ### Build Target Contract\n114: \n115: **Pattern**: `docker-build-<component>`\n116: \n117: **Input Variables**:\n118: - `DOCKER_TAG` (optional, default: `latest`)\n119: - `VERSION` (auto-detected from git)\n120: - `COMMIT_SHA` (auto-detected from git)\n121: \n122: **Behavior**:\n123: 1. Invoke `docker build` with component-specific Dockerfile\n124: 2. Pass build arguments: `VERSION`, `COMMIT_SHA`\n125: 3. Tag image with three tags: `DOCKER_TAG`, `COMMIT_SHA`, `VERSION`\n126: 4. Output success message with image name\n127: \n128: **Example**:\n129: ```bash\n130: make docker-build-workloadmanager DOCKER_TAG=v1.0.0\n131: ```\n132: \n133: ### Push Target Contract\n134: \n135: **Pattern**: `docker-push-<component>`\n136: \n137: **Prerequisites**: \n138: - Docker authentication configured for `DOCKER_REGISTRY`\n139: - Image exists locally (run build target first)\n140: \n141: **Behavior**:\n142: 1. Push all three tags to registry\n143: 2. Output confirmation messages\n144: \n145: **Example**:\n146: ```bash\n147: make docker-push-all DOCKER_REGISTRY=ghcr.io/volcano-sh\n148: ```\n149: \n150: ### Kind Load Target Contract\n151: \n152: **Pattern**: `kind-load-<component>`\n153: \n154: **Prerequisites**:\n155: - Kind cluster running\n156: - Image exists locally\n157: \n158: **Behavior**:\n159: 1. Load image into Kind cluster's containerd storage\n160: 2. Enable pod scheduling with local image\n161: \n162: **Example**:\n163: ```bash\n164: make kind-load-all\n165: ```\n166: \n167: ### Multi-architecture Build Contract\n168: \n169: **Pattern**: `docker-buildx-<component>`\n170: \n171: **Prerequisites**:\n172: - Docker Buildx enabled\n173: - Builder instance configured for multi-arch\n174: - Registry authentication\n175: \n176: **Platforms**: `linux/amd64`, `linux/arm64`\n177: \n178: **Behavior**:\n179: 1. Build multi-arch image using buildx\n180: 2. Push directly to registry (no local load)\n181: 3. Create manifest list with both architectures\n182: \n183: **Example**:\n184: ```bash\n185: make docker-buildx-router DOCKER_TAG=multi-arch-test\n186: ```\n187: \n188: ### Validate Target Contract\n189: \n190: **Pattern**: `docker-validate[-<component>]`\n191: \n192: **Prerequisites**:\n193: - Image exists locally\n194: \n195: **Behavior**:\n196: 1. Invoke `deployment/docker/test/validate.sh` with image name\n197: 2. Check image size, security configuration, labels\n198: 3. Report validation results\n199: \n200: **Example**:\n201: ```bash\n202: make docker-validate\n203: ```\n204: \n205: ### Test Target Contract\n206: \n207: **Targets**: `docker-test-build`, `docker-test-runtime`, `docker-test`\n208: \n209: **Prerequisites**:\n210: - Docker daemon running\n211: - Build scripts executable\n212: \n213: **Behavior**:\n214: 1. `docker-test-build`: Run build verification tests\n215: 2. `docker-test-runtime`: Run runtime behavior tests\n216: 3. Report pass/fail status\n217: \n218: **Example**:\n219: ```bash\n220: make docker-test\n221: ```\n222: \n223: ## Error Handling\n224: \n225: ### Variable Fallback Chain\n226: \n227: ```makefile\n228: # Git-based version detection with fallback\n229: VERSION ?= $(shell git describe --tags --always --dirty 2>/dev/null || echo \"dev\")\n230: \n231: # Commit SHA with fallback\n232: COMMIT_SHA ?= $(shell git rev-parse --short HEAD 2>/dev/null || echo \"unknown\")\n233: ```\n234: \n235: ### Error Suppression Patterns\n236: \n237: For cleanup operations, use `-` prefix to ignore failures:\n238: \n239: ```makefile\n240: docker-clean:\n241: \t-docker rmi $(WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG) 2>/dev/null || true\n242: ```\n243: \n244: ### Validation Error Handling\n245: \n246: ```bash\n247: #!/bin/bash\n248: # deployment/docker/test/validate.sh\n249: \n250: set -e  # Exit on first error\n251: \n252: IMAGE=\"$1\"\n253: \n254: if [ -z \"$IMAGE\" ]; then\n255:     echo \"Error: Image name required\"\n256:     exit 1\n257: fi\n258: \n259: # Check image exists\n260: if ! docker image inspect \"$IMAGE\" > /dev/null 2>&1; then\n261:     echo \"Error: Image $IMAGE not found\"\n262:     exit 1\n263: fi\n264: \n265: # Size check (example: max 200MB)\n266: SIZE=$(docker image inspect \"$IMAGE\" --format='{{.Size}}')\n267: MAX_SIZE=$((200 * 1024 * 1024))\n268: if [ \"$SIZE\" -gt \"$MAX_SIZE\" ]; then\n269:     echo \"Error: Image size exceeds limit (${SIZE} > ${MAX_SIZE})\"\n270:     exit 1\n271: fi\n272: ```\n273: \n274: ### Docker Command Error Handling\n275: \n276: All docker commands should handle failures gracefully:\n277: \n278: ```makefile\n279: docker-build-workloadmanager:\n280: \t@if ! docker build \\\n281: \t\t-f deployment/docker/Dockerfile \\\n282: \t\t--build-arg VERSION=$(VERSION) \\\n283: \t\t--build-arg COMMIT_SHA=$(COMMIT_SHA) \\\n284: \t\t-t $(WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG) \\\n285: \t\t.; then \\\n286: \t\techo \"Error: Build failed\"; \\\n287: \t\texit 1; \\\n288: \tfi\n289: ```\n290: \n291: ## Testing Strategy\n292: \n293: ### Unit Tests (Build Verification)\n294: \n295: **File**: `deployment/docker/test/build_test.sh`\n296: \n297: ```bash\n298: #!/bin/bash\n299: # Test 1: Verify Dockerfile syntax\n300: test_dockerfile_syntax() {\n301:     local dockerfile=\"$1\"\n302:     if ! docker build --check -f \"$dockerfile\" . 2>/dev/null; then\n303:         echo \"FAIL: Dockerfile syntax error: $dockerfile\"\n304:         return 1\n305:     fi\n306:     echo \"PASS: Dockerfile syntax valid: $dockerfile\"\n307: }\n308: \n309: # Test 2: Verify build arguments\n310: test_build_args() {\n311:     local image=$(docker build \\\n312:         -f deployment/docker/Dockerfile \\\n313:         --build-arg VERSION=test-version \\\n314:         --build-arg COMMIT_SHA=test-sha \\\n315:         -q .)\n316:     \n317:     # Verify labels\n318:     local version=$(docker inspect \"$image\" --format='{{index .Config.Labels \"version\"}}')\n319:     if [ \"$version\" != \"test-version\" ]; then\n320:         echo \"FAIL: Version label mismatch\"\n321:         return 1\n322:     fi\n323:     echo \"PASS: Build arguments applied correctly\"\n324: }\n325: \n326: # Run all tests\n327: test_dockerfile_syntax \"deployment/docker/Dockerfile\"\n328: test_dockerfile_syntax \"deployment/docker/Dockerfile.router\"\n329: test_dockerfile_syntax \"deployment/docker/Dockerfile.picod\"\n330: test_build_args\n331: ```\n332: \n333: ### Integration Tests (Runtime Verification)\n334: \n335: **File**: `deployment/docker/test/runtime_test.sh`\n336: \n337: ```bash\n338: #!/bin/bash\n339: # Test 1: Container startup\n340: test_container_startup() {\n341:     local container_id=$(docker run -d \"$IMAGE\" sleep 30)\n342:     if [ -z \"$container_id\" ]; then\n343:         echo \"FAIL: Container failed to start\"\n344:         return 1\n345:     fi\n346:     \n347:     # Wait for health check\n348:     sleep 5\n349:     if ! docker exec \"$container_id\" pgrep -x \"workloadmanager\" > /dev/null; then\n350:         echo \"FAIL: Process not running\"\n351:         docker rm -f \"$container_id\"\n352:         return 1\n353:     fi\n354:     \n355:     docker rm -f \"$container_id\"\n356:     echo \"PASS: Container startup successful\"\n357: }\n358: \n359: # Test 2: Environment variable injection\n360: test_env_vars() {\n361:     local container_id=$(docker run -d \\\n362:         -e REDIS_ADDR=\"redis:6379\" \\\n363:         -e REDIS_PASSWORD=\"test\" \\\n364:         \"$IMAGE\" sleep 30)\n365:     \n366:     local redis_addr=$(docker exec \"$container_id\" env | grep REDIS_ADDR)\n367:     if [ -z \"$redis_addr\" ]; then\n368:         echo \"FAIL: Environment variables not injected\"\n369:         docker rm -f \"$container_id\"\n370:         return 1\n371:     fi\n372:     \n373:     docker rm -f \"$container_id\"\n374:     echo \"PASS: Environment variables injected\"\n375: }\n376: ```\n377: \n378: ### Validation Tests\n379: \n380: **File**: `deployment/docker/test/validate.sh`\n381: \n382: ```bash\n383: #!/bin/bash\n384: IMAGE=\"$1\"\n385: \n386: echo \"Validating $IMAGE...\"\n387: \n388: # Test 1: Image exists\n389: echo -n \"Checking image exists... \"\n390: if docker image inspect \"$IMAGE\" > /dev/null 2>&1; then\n391:     echo \"PASS\"\n392: else\n393:     echo \"FAIL\"\n394:     exit 1\n395: fi\n396: \n397: # Test 2: Size check\n398: echo -n \"Checking image size... \"\n399: SIZE=$(docker image inspect \"$IMAGE\" --format='{{.Size}}')\n400: SIZE_MB=$((SIZE / 1024 / 1024))\n401: if [ \"$SIZE_MB\" -lt 200 ]; then\n402:     echo \"PASS (${SIZE_MB}MB)\"\n403: else\n404:     echo \"FAIL (${SIZE_MB}MB exceeds 200MB limit)\"\n405:     exit 1\n406: fi\n407: \n408: # Test 3: Required labels\n409: echo -n \"Checking labels... \"\n410: for label in version commit-sha; do\n411:     if ! docker inspect \"$IMAGE\" --format=\"{{index .Config.Labels \\\"$label\\\"}}\" | grep -q .; then\n412:         echo \"FAIL (missing $label)\"\n413:         exit 1\n414:     fi\n415: done\n416: echo \"PASS\"\n417: \n418: # Test 4: Security scan (trivy example)\n419: echo -n \"Running security scan... \"\n420: if command -v trivy > /dev/null; then\n421:     if trivy image --exit-code 1 \"$IMAGE\" > /dev/null 2>&1; then\n422:         echo \"PASS\"\n423:     else\n424:         echo \"FAIL (vulnerabilities found)\"\n425:         exit 1\n426:     fi\n427: else\n428:     echo \"SKIP (trivy not installed)\"\n429: fi\n430: \n431: echo \"\"\n432: echo \"Validation passed!\"\n433: ```\n434: \n435: ### Kind Integration Tests\n436: \n437: ```bash\n438: #!/bin/bash\n439: # Test: Load image to Kind and verify pod scheduling\n440: \n441: CLUSTER_NAME=\"agentcube-test\"\n442: \n443: # Create Kind cluster\n444: kind create cluster --name \"$CLUSTER_NAME\"\n445: \n446: # Load image\n447: make kind-load-workloadmanager\n448: \n449: # Deploy test pod\n450: kubectl apply -f - <<EOF\n451: apiVersion: v1\n452: kind: Pod\n453: metadata:\n454:   name: test-workloadmanager\n455: spec:\n456:   containers:\n457:   - name: workloadmanager\n458:     image: ghcr.io/volcano-sh/workloadmanager:latest\n459:   restartPolicy: Never\n460: EOF\n461: \n462: # Wait for pod to start\n463: kubectl wait --for=condition=Ready pod/test-workloadmanager --timeout=60s\n464: \n465: if [ $? -eq 0 ]; then\n466:     echo \"PASS: Image loaded and pod scheduled successfully\"\n467:     kind delete cluster --name \"$CLUSTER_NAME\"\n468:     exit 0\n469: else\n470:     echo \"FAIL: Pod failed to schedule\"\n471:     kind delete cluster --name \"$CLUSTER_NAME\"\n472:     exit 1\n473: fi\n474: ```\n475: \n476: ### Test Matrix\n477: \n478: | Test Category | Coverage | Frequency |\n479: |---------------|----------|-----------|\n480: | Build verification | 100% of Dockerfiles | Every build |\n481: | Runtime behavior | Critical paths | CI/CD |\n482: | Validation | Size, labels, security | Pre-push |\n483: | Kind integration | Full deployment cycle | CI/CD |\n484: \n485: ## Environment Configuration\n486: \n487: ### Required Environment Variables\n488: \n489: | Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n490: |----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n491: | `DOCKER_REGISTRY` | No | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh` | Container registry |\n492: | `DOCKER_TAG` | No | `latest` | Image tag |\n493: | `DOCKER_REGISTRY_USERNAME` | For push | - | Registry username |\n494: | `DOCKER_REGISTRY_PASSWORD` | For push | - | Registry password/token |\n495: \n496: ### Optional Environment Variables\n497: \n498: | Variable | Purpose |\n499: |----------|---------|\n500: | `VERSION` | Override auto-detected version |\n501: | `COMMIT_SHA` | Override auto-detected commit SHA |\n502: | `DOCKER_BUILDKIT` | Enable BuildKit (recommended: `1`) |\n503: | `DOCKER_BUILD_CONTEXT` | Custom build context path |\n504: \n505: ### Authentication Setup\n506: \n507: ```bash\n508: # GitHub Container Registry\n509: echo \"$GITHUB_TOKEN\" | docker login ghcr.io -u \"$GITHUB_USERNAME\" --password-stdin\n510: \n511: # Alternative: Use environment variables\n512: export DOCKER_REGISTRY_USERNAME=\"your-username\"\n513: export DOCKER_REGISTRY_PASSWORD=\"your-token\"\n514: ```\n515: \n516: ## File Structure\n517: \n518: ```\n519: root/\n520: ├── Makefile                          # Main build system (237 lines)\n521: ├── deployment/\n522: │   └── docker/\n523: │       ├── Dockerfile                # Workload Manager base image\n524: │       ├── Dockerfile.router         # Router image\n525: │       ├── Dockerfile.picod          # Picod image\n526: │       └── test/\n527: │           ├── validate.sh           # Image validation (size, security, labels)\n528: │           ├── build_test.sh         # Build verification tests\n529: │           ├── runtime_test.sh       # Runtime behavior tests\n530: │           └── kind_test.sh          # Kind cluster integration tests\n531: └── bin/                              # Build output directory\n532: ```\n533: \n534: ## Implementation Notes\n535: \n536: ### Version Detection\n537: \n538: The Makefile uses git to automatically detect version information:\n539: \n540: ```makefile\n541: VERSION ?= $(shell git describe --tags --always --dirty 2>/dev/null || echo \"dev\")\n542: COMMIT_SHA ?= $(shell git rev-parse --short HEAD 2>/dev/null || echo \"unknown\")\n543: ```\n544: \n545: **Fallback behavior**:\n546: - If git is not available: `VERSION=dev`, `COMMIT_SHA=unknown`\n547: - If in dirty working tree: `VERSION=<tag>-<commits>-g<sha>-dirty`\n548: - If no tags exist: `VERSION=<sha>`\n549: \n550: ### Image Tagging Strategy\n551: \n552: Each build produces three tags for flexibility:\n553: \n554: 1. **`DOCKER_TAG`** - Configurable tag (default: `latest`)\n555: 2. **`COMMIT_SHA`** - Immutable commit-based tag\n556: 3. **`VERSION`** - Git describe-based version tag\n557: \n558: This enables:\n559: - Development: Use `latest` tag\n560: - CI/CD: Use `COMMIT_SHA` for traceability\n561: - Releases: Use `VERSION` for semantic versioning\n562: \n563: ### Multi-architecture Support\n564: \n565: Buildx targets use the following configuration:\n566: \n567: ```makefile\n568: docker buildx build \\\n569:     --platform linux/amd64,linux/arm64 \\\n570:     --push \\\n571:     -t $(IMAGE):$(TAG) \\\n572:     .\n573: ```\n574: \n575: **Notes**:\n576: - `--push` required (multi-arch images cannot be loaded locally)\n577: - Requires buildx builder with multi-arch support\n578: - Creates manifest list automatically\n579: \n580: ### Kind Integration\n581: \n582: Kind load targets use:\n583: \n584: ```bash\n585: kind load docker-image $(IMAGE):$(TAG)\n586: ```\n587: \n588: **Limitations**:\n589: - Only loads single architecture (matches Kind node architecture)\n590: - Does not load multi-arch manifest lists\n591: - Image must exist in local Docker daemon first\n592: \n593: ### Cleanup Strategy\n594: \n595: The `docker-clean` target uses defensive deletion:\n596: \n597: ```makefile\n598: -docker rmi $(IMAGE):$(TAG) 2>/dev/null || true\n599: ```\n600: \n601: **Rationale**:\n602: - `-` prefix: Ignore command failure\n603: - `2>/dev/null`: Suppress error messages\n604: - `|| true`: Ensure Makefile continues even if image doesn't exist\n605: \n606: This makes cleanup idempotent and safe to run multiple times.\n607: \n608: ## Security Considerations\n609: \n610: 1. **Registry Authentication** - Use tokens, not passwords; store in CI/CD secrets\n611: 2. **Image Signing** - Consider implementing cosign or Docker Content Trust\n612: 3. **Vulnerability Scanning** - Integrate trivy or similar in CI/CD\n613: 4. **Build Isolation** - Use BuildKit for reproducible builds\n614: 5. **Secret Management** - Never hardcode secrets in Dockerfiles; use build secrets or multi-stage builds\n615: \n616: ## Dependencies\n617: \n618: | Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n619: |------------|---------|---------|\n620: | Docker | ≥20.10 | Container build and runtime |\n621: | Docker Buildx | ≥0.6 | Multi-architecture builds |\n622: | Kind | ≥0.17 | Local Kubernetes testing |\n623: | Git | ≥2.0 | Version detection |\n624: | Bash | ≥4.0 | Test scripts |\n625: | trivy | Optional | Security scanning |\n626: \n627: ## Migration Notes\n628: \n629: ### From Manual Docker Commands\n630: \n631: **Before**:\n632: ```bash\n633: docker build -f deployment/docker/Dockerfile -t ghcr.io/volcano-sh/workloadmanager:latest .\n634: docker push ghcr.io/volcano-sh/workloadmanager:latest\n635: ```\n636: \n637: **After**:\n638: ```bash\n639: make docker-build-workloadmanager\n640: make docker-push-workloadmanager\n641: ```\n642: \n643: **Benefits**:\n644: - Automatic version tagging\n645: - Consistent build arguments\n646: - Integrated validation and testing\n647: \n648: ### Breaking Changes\n649: \n650: None - this is a new implementation.\n651: \n652: ## Examples\n653: \n654: ### Development Workflow\n655: \n656: ```bash\n657: # Build all images\n658: make docker-build-all\n659: \n660: # Load to Kind for testing\n661: make kind-load-all\n662: \n663: # Run tests\n664: make docker-test\n665: \n666: # Deploy to Kind\n667: kubectl apply -k manifests/\n668: ```\n669: \n670: ### CI/CD Pipeline\n671: \n672: ```bash\n673: # Build and validate\n674: make docker-build-all\n675: make docker-validate\n676: \n677: # Push to registry\n678: echo \"$GITHUB_TOKEN\" | docker login ghcr.io -u \"$GITHUB_USERNAME\" --password-stdin\n679: make docker-push-all\n680: \n681: # Load to test cluster\n682: kind create cluster --name test\n683: make kind-load-all\n684: \n685: # Run integration tests\n686: ./testing/integration/run_tests.sh\n687: ```\n688: \n689: ### Multi-architecture Release\n690: \n691: ```bash\n692: # Build and push multi-arch images\n693: make docker-buildx-all DOCKER_TAG=v1.0.0\n694: \n695: # Verify manifest\n696: docker manifest inspect ghcr.io/volcano-sh/workloadmanager:v1.0.0\n697: ```\n698: \n699: ### Clean Build\n700: \n701: ```bash\n702: # Clean local images\n703: make docker-clean\n704: \n705: # Rebuild from scratch\n706: make docker-build-all DOCKER_TAG=dev\n707: ```\n708: \n709: ## References\n710: \n711: - `Makefile` - Current implementation (237 lines)\n712: - `deployment/docker/Dockerfile` - Workload Manager Dockerfile\n713: - `deployment/docker/Dockerfile.router` - Router Dockerfile\n714: - `deployment/docker/Dockerfile.picod` - Picod Dockerfile\n715: - AR-030 - Helm Chart deployment (uses images built by this Makefile)\n716: - AR-031 - RBAC configuration (independent of build system)\n\n(End of file - total 716 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Design: AR-033 — Makefile 构建目标体系\n\n## Overview\n\nThis document describes the technical implementation for the Makefile build target system in AgentCube. The Makefile provides a comprehensive set of targets for building, pushing, testing, and managing Docker container images across multiple components (Workload Manager, Router, Picod), with support for multi-architecture builds, Kind cluster integration, and image validation.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Component Structure\n\n```\nroot/\n├── Makefile                          # Main build system\n├── deployment/\n│   └── docker/\n│       ├── Dockerfile                # Workload Manager Dockerfile\n│       ├── Dockerfile.router         # Router Dockerfile\n│       ├── Dockerfile.picod          # Picod Dockerfile\n│       ├── test/\n│       │   ├── validate.sh           # Image validation script","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-033/design/design.md","time":{"start":1775882670402,"end":1775882670424}}}}
